OL,3,C'People are living in garden sheds':
OL,4,CThe reality of the housing crisis
OL,6,FCathy Gallienne explains: "There are
OL,7,Fsituations where people are living in
OL,8,Fgarden sheds and key workers in
OL,9,Ftemporary accommodation, to local
OL,10,Fpeople needing to move because their
OL,11,Flandlord has decided to sell or the
OL,12,Fapartment is too small because they're
OL,13,Fstarting a family. There are a lot of
OL,14,Fstories and everyone has a genuine
OL,15,Freason for moving."
OL,17,FOne prospective tenant in Guernsey
OL,18,Fclaims several landlords rejected her
OL,19,Fbecause she was expecting a baby.
